verbose_text: To examine whether endogenous phagocytes were responsible for the loss of tau aggregate containing neurons that occurs over 2-3 weeks, we eliminated the phagocytes by treatment (4 hr) with leucine methyl ester (LME), followed by an overnight incubation to ensure death of phagocytes.
